author: Written by: Sam Winstrom, Assignment Editor
title: NOPD investigating St. Roch shooting
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - A man shot in St. Roch Saturday is expected to survive.
According to NOPD, a man sustained a non-life-threatening gunshot wound to the body in the 2700 block of N. Tonti Street just before 3 p.m. on Oct. 10.
Investigators are on the scene and no further information is currently available.
Anyone with information on this incident is asked to call CRIMESTOPPERS at 504-822-1111.
